      "message": "[warning] Line 338: This skips rebuilding/updating the foreground call notification whenever the call status is unchanged after the service has started. Call notifications contain more than just `CallStatus` (participants/contact data, actions, screen share state, etc.), so those updates can be dropped while the UI still shows stale content. Only suppress a foreground-service start when no notification-visible state changed, or still update the existing notification without restarting the service. For example, track a richer notification key or remove this early return:\n```suggestion\n                lastCallNotificationStatus[id] \u003d status\n```\nThen let the existing notification path update the service/notification.",
