      "message": "[warning] Line 378: `safeStart` checks only `currentCalls.isEmpty()`, so a delayed Telecom-state emission for an old conference can still start the foreground service after that specific call was removed, as long as another call exists. Because `callNotifications[nid]` is populated inside `start()`, this can queue and start a stale notification/call id. Check that the same conference id is still current before starting.\n```suggestion\n                    if (!currentCalls.containsKey(id)) {\n                        Log.w(TAG, \"Skipping call foreground service start: call is no longer active\")\n                    } else try {\n```\nThis avoids racing disconnected calls against later active calls.",
